column4: Cloud business boosts Microsoft's quarterly revenue  shares rise
column5: Sharp growth in its commercial cloud computing business helped lift Microsoft Corp's  quarterly revenue above Wall Street's expectations  sending the technology company's shares up more than 4 percent in after-hours trading.

column4: UPDATE 2-Cloud business boosts Microsoft's quarterly revenue  shares rise
column5: July 19 Sharp growth in its commercial cloud computing business helped lift Microsoft Corp's  quarterly revenue above Wall Street's expectations  sending the technology company's shares up more than 4 percent in after-hours trading.

column4: BRIEF-Microsoft reports quarterly GAAP earnings per share $0.39
column5: * Quarterly diluted earnings per share was $0.39 GAAP  and $0.69 non-GAAP

column4: Tesla shortens web address  mum on formal name change
column5: DETROIT Electric vehicle maker Tesla Motors Inc has changed its internet address from teslamotors.com to tesla.com  hinting at a possible company name change as part of CEO Elon Musk's latest and still undisclosed "master plan."
